                <head>143. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Most of the correspondence between President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> and President <persName corresp="#p_DEGC1">de
                        Gaulle</persName> in October focused on the question of a possible summit
                    meeting. In his letter of September 30, <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> reported on the visit of Premier <persName
                        corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName> to the United States September
                    15–28, and told <persName corresp="#p_DEGC1">de Gaulle</persName> that his talks
                    with the Soviet leader removed many of the objections he personally had to a
                    summit conference. Regarding this letter and <persName corresp="#p_DEGC1">de
                        Gaulle</persName>’s reply of October 8, see <ref
                        target="frus1958-60v09#d18fn1">volume IX, Document 18, footnote 1</ref>, and
                        <ref target="frus1958-60v09#d24fn3">Document 24, footnote 3</ref>. Regarding
                        <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>’s letter to <persName
                        corresp="#p_DEGC1">de Gaulle</persName>, October 9, see <ref
                        target="frus1958-60v09#d24">
                        <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., Document 24, footnote 2</ref>. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>’s letters to <persName
                        corresp="#p_DEGC1">de Gaulle</persName> of October 16 and 21 are <ref
                        target="frus1958-60v09#d27">
                        <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., Documents 27</ref> and <ref
                        target="frus1958-60v09#d32">32</ref>. Regarding his letter of October 28,
                    see <ref target="frus1958-60v09#d38fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., Document 38, footnote 2</ref>. <persName
                        corresp="#p_DEGC1">de Gaulle</persName>’s letters to <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> of October 20 and 26 about a
                    possible summit meeting are <ref target="frus1958-60v09#d30">
                        <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., Documents 30</ref> and <ref
                        target="frus1958-60v09#d36">36</ref>.</p>
            </div>
